    "narrative": "The Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is anchored today by **Mickey Moniak**, who presents our highest ceiling at a 75.98 efficiency score. His matchup against Glasnow is elevated by a massive 14% park factor boost and a prime #2 spot in the order, offering significant volume for both R and RBI. **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.72) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (72.09) follow closely, both benefitting from favorable matchups against the vulnerable arm of Wacha. While the latter face potential volatility due to a 31% rain risk, their high SP skill interaction scores make them essential plays for chasing counting stats. **Austin Riley** also warrants strong consideration (71.42) as he capitalizes on a high SP skill disparity against Walker, providing a reliable baseline for power output.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Alex Freeland**, whose 58.63 score fell just short of the threshold. While he benefits from a 14% park boost, his #9 position in the order significantly suppressed his expected production relative to the rest of the utility corps. Meanwhile, **Corbin Carroll** remains a critical component of our strategy; despite facing a tougher opponent in Fisher, his 62.60 score is buoyed by an elite 85% SB opportunity window. We are closely monitoring the 31% rain risk affecting **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, and **Giancarlo Stanton**. If the weather forces a postponement, we are prepared to pivot to **Jose Caballero** or **Josh Naylor**, though they currently sit on the bench as the optimizer prioritized the higher projected efficiency of our active starters. **Luis Campusano** remains our lowest-rated start (42.06); we are holding him in the lineup pending official verification of his #8 spot, but he remains on a short leash as we balance positional necessity against his sub-optimal platoon metrics.",
